name: Elise
title: the Spider Queen
lore: Elise is a deadly predator who dwells in a shuttered, lightless palace, deep within the oldest city of Noxus. Once mortal, she was the mistress of a powerful house, but the bite of a vile demigod transformed her into something beautiful, yet utterly inhumanâ€”a spider-like creature, drawing unsuspecting prey into her web. To maintain her eternal youth, Elise now prefers to feed upon the naive and the faithless, and there are few who can resist her seductions.
blurb: Elise is a deadly predator who dwells in a shuttered, lightless palace, deep within the oldest city of Noxus. Once mortal, she was the mistress of a powerful house, but the bite of a vile demigod transformed her into something beautiful, yet utterly...
allytips: Spider Form is most effective at finishing off enemies with low health; Human Form's Neurotoxin does more damage to healthy foes.
When in Spider Form, Spiderlings will attack the target that Elise uses Venomous Bite on.
Elise's Spider Form and Spider Form abilities do not cost mana and can be prioritized when you are trying to conserve mana.
enemytips: Elise's Spider Form is more dangerous when you are at low health, and her Human Form more potent when you are at high health.
Rappel will only move Elise straight up and down unless she can descend upon an enemy unit.
Rappel has a long cooldown. Elise is vulnerable after she has used it.

riot_spells.name: Neurotoxin / Venomous Bite
riot_spells.description:
Human Form: Deals damage based upon how high the target's Health is.

Spider Form: Lunges at an enemy and deals damage based upon how low their Health is.
riot_spells.tooltip: Deals magic damage equal to {{ e1 }} plus {{ e6 }}% (+{{ a1 }}%) of the target's current health. Maximum bonus against monsters: {{ e2 }}.

riot_spells.name: Volatile Spiderling / Skittering Frenzy
riot_spells.description:
Human Form: Releases a venom-gorged Spiderling that explodes when it nears a target.

Spider Form: Elise and her Spiderlings gain Attack Speed.
riot_spells.tooltip: Summons a venom-gorged Spiderling that moves to target location and explodes, dealing {{ e3 }} (+{{ a1 }}) Magic Damage when it nears an enemy or after 3 seconds.

riot_spells.name: Cocoon / Rappel
riot_spells.description:
Human Form: Stuns the first enemy unit hit and reveals them if they are not stealthed.

Spider Form: Elise and her Spiderlings ascend into the air and then descend upon target enemy. After descending on an enemy target, Elise's bonus damage and healing from Spider Queen is increased.
riot_spells.tooltip: Stuns the first enemy hit for {{ e5 }} seconds and reveals them if they are not stealthed.

riot_spells.name: Spider Form
riot_spells.description: Transforms into a menacing spider, reducing her attack range in exchange for movement speed, new abilities, and a Spiderling swarm that will attack her foes.
riot_spells.tooltip:
Elise transforms into a menacing spider, sacrificing 425 attack range in exchange for {{ e3 }} movement speed and access to arachnid abilities. All dormant Spiderlings are awakened and will attack nearby foes.

Spiderlings: Spiderlings deal {{ e1 }} (+{{ a2 }}) damage and take {{ e4 }}% reduced damage from multi-target abilities.

riot_passive.name: Spider Queen
riot_passive.description:
Human Form: When Elise's abilities hit an enemy, she gains a dormant Spiderling.

Spider Form: Basic attacks deal bonus magic damage and restore health to Elise.

i1.name: Spider Queen
i1.blurb: Human Form: When Elise's abilities hit an enemy, she gains a dormant Spiderling. Spider Form: Basic attacks deal bonus magic damage and restore health to Elise.
i1.description: {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']] - Innate:}} When '''Elise's''' [[Champion ability|abilities]] hits a target she gains one dormant ''Spiderling'', up to {{pp|4|showtype=true|type = [[File:EliseSquare.png|20px|link=]] Human Form's Rank|2 to 5}}.
i1.description2: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Innate:}} '''Elise's''' [[basic attack]]s deal {{pp|4|showtype=true|type = [[File:Spider Form.png|20px|link=]] Spider Form's Rank|10 to 40|color=magic damage}} {{as|(+ 30% AP)}} {{tip|magic damage|{{as|'''bonus''' magic damage}}}} and {{tip|heal}} her for {{sti|health|icononly=true}} {{pp|4|showtype=true|type = [[File:Spider Form.png|20px|link=]] Spider Form's Rank|4 to 10|color=health}} {{as|(+ 10% AP)}} {{as|health}} [[On-hit effect|on-hit]].
i1.notes:
* ''Elise'' will always begin the game and respawn with maximum available ''Spiderlings'' stored.
* ''Elise's'' {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']]}} ability casts can only store one ''Spiderling'' each.
* ''Spider Form's'' basic attacks will apply other [[on-hit effect]]s and can {{tip|critical strike|critically strike}} as normal (the '''bonus''' damage does not).
** ''Spider Form's'' bonus damage does not affect structures.
** ''Spider Form's'' heal will not trigger when attacking structures.
** {{Pending for test}}: ''Spider Form's'' relationship with {{ai|Counter Strike|Jax|dodge}}, {{ai|Spirit's Refuge|Shen|block}}, and {{tip|blind}}.

q1.name: Neurotoxin
q1.blurb: Human Form: Deals damage based upon how high the target's Health is.
q1.description: {{sbc|{{cci|EliseSquare.png|Elise#Human Form|'''Human Form'''}} - Active:}} '''Elise''' fires toxin at the target enemy unit, dealing {{as|magic damage}}, capped against {{tip|monster|monsters}}.
q1.leveling: {{st|Magic Damage|{{ap|40 to 180}} {{as|(+ 4% {{as|(+ 3% per 100 AP)}} of target's '''current''' health)|health}}|Max. Monster Damage|{{ap|115 to 355}}}}

q2.name: Venomous Bite
q2.blurb: Spider Form: Lunges at an enemy and deals damage based upon how low their Health is.
q2.description: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' {{tip|dashes}} to the target enemy and bites them, dealing {{as|magic damage}}, capped against monsters.
q2.description2: If there are active {{ai|Spider Queen|Elise|spiderlings}} or a {{ai|Volatile Spiderling|Elise|votatile spiderling}} nearby, they will {{tip|dash}} alongside '''Elise''' towards ''Venomous Bite's'' target and reprioritize them.
q2.leveling: {{st|Magic Damage|{{ap|70 to 230}} {{as|(+ 8% {{as|(+ 3% per 100 AP)}} of target's '''missing''' health)|health}}|Max. Monster Damage|{{ap|145 to 405}}}}
q2.notes:
* ''Venomous Bite'' cannot be used to cross walls or impassable terrain.
** The target will be damaged regardless.
*** {{ai|Spider Queen|Elise|Spiderlings}} can cross walls and terrain to reach ''Venomous Bite's'' target and will attack provided Elise stays within their leash range.

w1.name: Volatile Spiderling
w1.blurb: Human Form: Releases a venom-gorged Spiderling that explodes when it nears a target.
w1.description: {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' summons a venom-gorged spider for 3 seconds, which moves in the target direction.
w1.description2: The spider explodes upon contact with an enemy unit or at the end of its lifespan, dealing {{as|magic damage}} to nearby enemies.
w1.description3: If the spider does not hit an enemy before reaching the target location, it re-targets and chases down a nearby enemy, prioritizing {{tip|champion|champions}}. The spider gains {{sti|ms|{{as|'''bonus''' movement speed}}}}, based on its proximity to its target.
w1.notes: *If ''Volatile Spiderling'' dashes to a target due to {{ai|Venomous Bite|Elise}}, it will not expire before finishing its jump.

w2.name: Skittering Frenzy
w2.blurb: Spider Form: Elise and her Spiderlings gain Attack Speed.
w2.description: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Passive:}} '''Elise's''' {{ai|Spider Queen|Elise|Spiderlings}} gain {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}}.
w2.description2: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' and her {{ai|Spider Queen|Elise|Spiderlings}} gain {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}} for 3 seconds.
w2.notes:
* ''Skittering Frenzy'' has no cast time and does not interrupt ''Elise's'' previous orders.
* ''Elise'' loses the attack speed bonus immediately when turning back to {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']]}}.
** But if she is able to transform back in less than 3 seconds (only via sufficient [[cooldown reduction]]) she gets the bonus back for its remaining duration.

e1.name: Cocoon
e1.blurb: Human Form: Stuns the first enemy unit hit and reveals them if they are not stealthed.
e1.description: {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' fires a web in the target direction, granting {{tip|sight}} of the first enemy hit for 1 second and {{tip|stun|stunning}} them.

e2.name: Rappel
e2.blurb: Spider Form: Elise and her Spiderlings ascend into the air and then descend upon target enemy.
e2.description: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' lifts up into the air, becoming {{tip|untargetable}} for up to 2 seconds and {{tip|sight|revealing}} the area for the duration. While she's in the air she can select a target to instantly descend upon.
e2.description2: If cast directly on an enemy, '''Elise''' automatically descends upon them after 1 second. Upon landing, '''Elise's''' {{ai|Spider Queen|Elise}} bonuses are increased for 5 seconds.
e2.notes:
* When ''Elise'' casts ''Rappel'' a circle shows the area in which a target or location can be selected.
*''Elise'' only gains an increase in her passive bonuses if she directly targets an enemy with ''Rappel''.
** Elise cannot descend outside the bounds of this circle.
* Elise can cast ''Rappel'' on any targetable enemy unit ([[minion]]s, [[monster]]s, [[champion]]s, [[Champion summoned units|pets]], wards, and traps (provided she has {{tip|true sight}})).
*If Eliseâ€™s target is closer than Rappelâ€™s max range, Elise will attempt to position herself behind that target.
*Eliseâ€™s descending location is determined upon target-cast. Eliseâ€™s descending location does not change after being determined, even if her target moves.

r1.name: Spider Form / Human Form
r1.blurb: Transforms into a menacing spider, reducing her attack range in exchange for movement speed, new abilities, and a Spiderling swarm that will attack her foes.
r1.description2: {{sbc|[[File:EliseSquare.png|'''Human Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Human Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Human Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' transforms into a menacing spider, gaining {{sti|ms|{{as|25 '''bonus''' movement speed}}}}, {{tip|melee}} basic attacks with 125 {{sti|range}}, and access to her arachnid abilities. Additionally, '''Elise''' unleashes all stored ''Spiderlings''.
r1.description3: {{sbc|[[File:Spider_Form.png|'''Spider Form'''|20px|link=Elise#Spider Form|border]] [[Elise#Spider Form / Human Form|'''Spider Form''']] - Active:}} '''Elise''' transforms into her human form, gaining {{tip|ranged}} basic attacks, and access to her human abilities. Additionally, '''Elise''' stores all unleashed ''Spiderlings''.
r1.description4: '''Elise''' begins with one rank in ''Spider Form / Human Form'' and can increase it at levels 6, 11, and 16.
r1.notes:
* Both ''Spider Form'' and ''Human Form'' have no cast time and do not interrupt ''Elise's'' previous orders.
** ''Spider Form'' and ''Human Form'' have separate cooldowns.
* Neither transformation counts as an activation for the purposes of items such as {{ii|Tear of the Goddess}}, {{nie|Spellblade}}, and {{ai|Force Pulse|Kassadin}}.
